 "incline_code": "Slab & Vertical",
 "intro_html": "Stetind is a huge granite pillar rising 1329 m out of Tysfjord. Voted Norways national Mountain it’s an iconic sight. The South Pilar route or Sydpillaren, offers some challenging climbing, especially towards the top with a couple of N6- graded pitches which roughly equate to HVS/E1. In total it’s a 14 pitch climb that is described as one of Norway’s finest climbs and it’s a classic alpine test piece. Getting down actually requires reversing the Original Route (graded n4),  it will require ropework in sections.",
